      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. i guess what i'm looking for is how this actually manifested in history. like, when you talk about the \"evolution\" part, does that mean these primitive structures were basically just stepping stones towards what we consider civilization today? if we look at how certain groups developed differently, was the path to being a \"modern\" society basically just a matter of following that same trajectory?",
