      "content": "i get that, but when historians talk about the \"civilizing mission\" or the way certain cultures were seen as \"uncivilized\" or \"lesser\" during the era of colonial expansion, wasn't that because they actually saw a lack of these modern structures? like, if a group didn't have the same level of technological or institutional complexity as Western Europe, was it fair to categorize them as being at a lower stage of human development?",
